    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We have a pre-existing process flow for password change, please see this function.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-go/blob/7e1a894ab824904f0c90acbc307955940ef17800/mobile/status.go#L833-L839\r\n\r\nMy formalised recommendation for the implementation of this functionality is as follows:\r\n\r\n> We could encode in lower case first. If that validates then all is good. Else encode in uppercase, if that validates, auth, then change password. Else login fails\r\n\r\nI'd imagine the code to look something like below:\r\n\r\n```go\r\n\r\n\t// normalise the hex encoding prefix\r\n\tif password[:2] != \"0x\" {\r\n\t\tpassword = \"0x\" + password\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\t// parse the password string to lowercase\r\n\tpassword = strings.ToLower(password)\r\n\r\n\t// authentication\r\n\r\n\t// If auth is fine, return\r\n\r\n\t// Else parse password string to uppercase\r\n\tpassword = \"0x\" + strings.ToUpper(password[2:])\r\n\t\r\n\t// reattempt authentication\r\n\t\r\n\t// if success \r\n\r\n\terr := b.ChangeDatabasePassword(KeyUID, password, newPassword)\r\n\t\r\n\t// else fail authentication\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn this case you don't need to version your passwords, you just normalise the password and rekey only if normalisation fails.\r\n\r\nWhat do you think?",
